reactions.name: Biomass reaction (batch, anaerobic and microaerobic conditions)

notes.notes: Difference between aerobic and anaerobic biomass reaction is the absence of heme and sphingolipid species requiring oxygen. Ergosterol (EX_ergst_e) and unsaturated fatty acid (EX_hdcea_e and EX_ocdcea_e) have to be supplemented in the media as reported in the literature. There is no degradation pathway for ergosterol and fatty acid cannot be degraded without oxygen so it is safe to set the nutrient supply unconstrained. Nicotinate (EX_nac_e) and pantothenate (EX_pnto__R_e) need to be supplied too as nutrients, as part of YNB media commonly used in yeast experiments for both aerobic and anaerobic conditions.
